labctl - iximiuz Labs command line interface.

Usage:
  labctl [command]

Available Commands:
  api          Send requests to iximiuz Labs API
  auth         Authenticate the current CLI session with iximiuz Labs
  challenge    Solve DevOps challenges from the comfort of your terminal
  completion   Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  content      Author and manage content (challenge, tutorial, course, etc.)
  cp           Copy files to and from the target playground
  expose       Expose HTTP(s) ports and web terminals for a running playground
  help         Help about any command
  playground   List, start and stop playgrounds
  port-forward Forward one or more local or remote ports to a running playground
  ssh          Start SSH session to the target playground
  ssh-proxy    Start SSH proxy to the playground's machine
  tutorial     Follow tutorials from the comfort of your local command line
  version      Print the version of labctl

Flags:
      --endpoint string    iximiuz Labs API endpoint URL
  -h, --help               help for labctl
  -l, --log-level string   log level for labctl ("debug" | "info" | "warn" | "error" | "fatal") (default "info")
  -v, --version            version for labctl

Use "labctl [command] --help" for more information about a command.
